Mixxx_Indicator 🐧🎧
The "On-Air" visual assistant for Mixxx DJs on Linux.
Developed because "impossible" is just a challenge, not an answer. This tool provides a floating, always-on-top visual indicator that changes color based on your actual streaming status.
What it does

    Automatic Startup: Launches Mixxx automatically if it's not already running.
    Smart Instance Control: Prevents multiple instances of Mixxx from opening.
    Live Status Monitoring:
        🔴 RED: Mixxx is open, but you are not streaming (or the connection dropped).
        🟢 GREEN: You are actively connected and streaming to a server.
    Auto-Cleanup: The indicator automatically closes when you exit Mixxx.
    Always on Top: Stays visible even when you are focused on other windows (like Second Life viewers, Firestorm, etc.).

System Requirements

    OS: Linux (Tested on Mint Cinnamon, should work on any Debian-based distro).
    Software: Mixxx (obviously!).
    Dependencies: Python3, python3-tk (for graphics), and iproute2 (for network checking).
    Note: The installer handles these for you!

Installation
The easiest way to get the Mixxx_Indicator is to use the provided installer script:

    Download the install_mixxx_indicator.sh script.
    Right-click the file and select Properties.
    Go to the Permissions tab and check "Allow executing file as program".
    Double-click the script and select "Run in Terminal" (or run ./install_mixxx_indicator.sh from your terminal).
    Enter your password when prompted to install the necessary libraries.

A shortcut named "Mixxx Indicator" will appear on your desktop.
How to use
Just double-click the Mixxx Indicator on your desktop. It will start Mixxx and the status light. You can drag the circle anywhere on your screen.
